LADDER STYLE HIIT ⚡️

say hello to one of my favorite styles of training - THE LADDER 🪜

if you’ve done it…you know that it’s a love/hate kind of thing 😤 This working set is from one of the week 5 workouts - it was killer but SOOOOO good. Here’s how it works 👇🏼

Pick however many different types of exercises you want. I like to pick two - in this case, box jumps + kettlebell swings!

Start at 10 reps of each. Then, go down 9 reps of each. Then 8…7…6…all the way down the ladder until you hit 1 rep of each exercise. Try not to rest - instead, PACE yourself! It’s as tedious and painful as it sounds 🤣

My favorite part about this style of workout: it gets EASIER every single round! Before you know it, you’re at 6 reps and mentally it feels like cake. YOU GOT THIS!

Try it & let me know what ya think! For more workouts like this, download me @makayla_utter’s training app by clicking the link in my bio. The first 7 days is FREE! 💪🏼

#hiit #hiitworkout #momworkout #athomeworkouts #athomeworkouts

BABY FRIENDLY BLENDER MUFFINS 👶🏼

A quick, healthy & EASY breakfast or snack idea for your little one!

INGREDIENTS:
1 cup pumpkin purée (or applesauce)
2 bananas
4 eggs
1/4 cup coconut oil 
3 TB maple syrup 
1 tsp. vanilla extract 
2 tsp. cinnamon or pumpkin pie spice 
1 TB baking powder 
1/4 tsp salt
2.5 cups oats

INSTRUCTIONS:
Throw all of the ingredients in a blender & blend until completely smooth. Pour into greased muffin tin & bake at 350 degrees for 18 minutes 👌🏼

Makes 12 muffins 😋

BABY-FRIENDLY HEALTHY CHICKEN NUGGETS 🐔👶🏼

Ingredients:
- 1 lb. ground chicken (or turkey!)
- 1 cup broccoli
- 1 cup cauliflower 
- 2 eggs
- onion powder, garlic powder, salt + pepper (we love using @littlepalates seasonings)
- 1 cup panko bread crumbs 

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Rice cauliflower & broccoli in food processor until fully chopped
2. In a large bowl, add riced veggies, ground chicken, seasonings & 1 egg. Massage through with hands until all ingredients are fully combined. Mold into nuggets and set aside on baking sheet. 
3. In a small bowl, prepare egg wash. Whisk together 1 egg and 1/4 cup water.
4. In a shallow bowl or dish, combine bread crumbs & seasonings. 
5. Take each nugget, dip in the egg wash & roll in bread crumbs. 
6. Bake in an airfryer at 390 degrees for 10-12 minutes.  If using an oven, bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

Store in fridge or flash freeze to batch! Enjoy! 👌🏼

Our Morning Routine 🤘🏻

We are big routine people, but have also learned that prioritizing responsibilities over routines is very important to us. 

Most days look like this…

I wake up at 5am and prepare for my morning run. Remi (our youngest dog) joins me for the first two miles. Ryder (our oldest dog) refuses to participate. 

Stef gets Charli up and ready as she “usually” wakes up while I’m running. 

After I return from my run I eat breakfast and start preparing Charli’s breakfast too. The go-to is fruit, milk and french toast/pancakes. She gives half of it to the dogs 🐶 

While I’m eating breakfast with Charli, Stef heads into our garage gym to hit a workout or class on her soulcycle bike.

Charli and I go grab a coffee, play, read books or take a stroll around the neighborhood while Stef is making breakfast after her workout.

We each get to train, eat and spend quality time with our baby girl. 

This is what works for us (at this point in our lives) and sets the foundation for a strong day 👊🏻

MY MUSCLE BUILDING MUST-HAVES 💪🏼

Mom strength is a real thing yall - I feel like I have more muscle & strength now than I did before having charli! Here are some of the things I’ve implemented that have helped me gain & maintain muscle:

5G OF CREATINE PER DAY // creatine is a HOT topic right now in the women’s health world - for a good reason! It’s something we should ALL be taking. It can improve performance, increase strength & muscle mass & can also improve mood and cognitive function.

3-4 STRENGTH TRAINING SESSION PER WEEK // I’ve found that 3-4 strength training sessions a week is my sweet spot for feeling good, recovering well & maintaining/building muscle. Most of my sessions are right around 30 minutes - that’s all you need! You can get ALL of my strength workouts in @makayla_utter & I’s app 👌🏼

PRIORITIZING PROTEIN // I aim for 100g-150g per day. It’s the foundation of all of my meals & snacks. @bpnsupps whey protein definitely helps with that!

2-3 CARDIO SESSIONS PER WEEK // I will *always* incorporate cardio into my training schedule because I love it & the health/cardiovascular benefits. The key to cardio is finding a type that you love - for me, that’s spin!

STAYING CONSISTENTLY GOOD OVER OCCASIONALLY GREAT // this is probably the most important one! No day is ever perfect. I’ve seen the best results with being consistently good when it comes to my diet & exercise rather than stressing for perfection. Perfection isn’t sustainable! So give me the bread, cookies, dinners out & cocktails in moderation 👏🏼
